{"id":"1008.5346","submitter":"Ivan Mukha","authors":"I. Mukha, E. Roeckl, H.Grawe and S. Tabor","title":"Comment on \"Reviewing the evidence for two-proton emission from the\n  high-spin isomer in $^{94}$Ag\"","comments":"2 pages, 0 figures","journal-ref":null,"doi":null,"report-no":null,"categories":"nucl-ex","license":"http://creativecommons.org/licenses/publicdomain/","abstract":"  A recent publication [D.G. Jenkins, Phys. Rev. C \\textbf{80}, 054303 (2009)]\nclaims to discredit the experimental observation of two-proton decay of the\n(21$^+$) high-spin isomer in $^{94}$Ag [I. Mukha \\emph{et al.,} Nature (London)\n\\textbf{439}, 298 (2006)]. Its conclusion, which would require a\nreestablishment of the two-proton emission, is made on the basis of unwarranted\nassumptions by Jenkins concerning the data analysis of the original work. We\nprovide proof that these assumptions do not correspond to reality, and that\ntherefore the conclusion of the paper is misleading.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 31 Aug 2010 15:58:34 GMT"}],"update_date":"2010-09-01"}
